<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tomorrow the US Supreme Court will hear argume=
nts in a case about whether the US Securities and Exchange Commission can f=
ine people without a jury trial. The SEC can bring =E2=80=9Cadministrative =
proceedings=E2=80=9D in its own in-house courts, in front of SEC employees =
called administrative law judges, rather than bringing them in regular cour=
ts. A lot of people think that this is unfair, and in the political and leg=
al climate of 2023, arguments like =E2=80=9Cthis administrative agency has =
too much power to regulate=E2=80=9D go a lot further than they used to.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so a guy named George Jarkesy allegedly di=
d some quite garden-variety fraud with <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
