<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/33512585.284432/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjcvb3BlbmFpLWlzLXN0aWxsLWFuLTg2LWJpbGxpb24tb=
m9ucHJvZml0P2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMjgyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRt=
X3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTEyOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHV=
mZiNmb290ZXItcmVmLWZvb3Rub3RlLTI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4a31471d" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>  I wrote out a=C2=A0list</a> of reasons that you might have updated your =
valuation of OpenAI over the past two weeks. You might, I argued, have busi=
ness or governance or regulatory reasons to think that OpenAI is worth=C2=
=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>than the $86 billion it was worth two weeks ago.=C2=
=A0Or you=C2=A0might have business or governance or regulatory reasons to t=
hink it is worth=C2=A0<em>less</em>. I also suggested that there might be t=
echnological, development-of-artificial-general-intelligence=C2=A0reasons i=
t is worth more: The boardroom coup that led to Sam Altman=E2=80=99s brief =
firing seems to have been precipitated in part by OpenAI=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=9Cpowerful artificial intelligence discovery=E2=80=9D that allowed it to b=
uild a model called Q* that =E2=80=9Cwas able to solve math problems that i=
t hadn=E2=80=99t seen before.=E2=80=9D I wrote: =E2=80=9CIf you were willin=
g to buy OpenAI stock at an $86 billion valuation as a bet that it would de=
velop increasingly powerful AI models, evidence that it has in fact develop=
ed increasingly powerful AI models should cause you to increase your valuat=
ion.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a footnote, I wrote that =E2=80=9Cfor symme=
try I want an answer like =E2=80=98less than $86 billion, for discovery of =
artificial general intelligence reasons,=E2=80=99=C2=A0but I have trouble c=
oming up with a good one.=E2=80=9D Of course that was meant as a prompt to =
my readers. I got a few answers I want to share with you. One possibility, =
which I got=C2=A0first=C2=A0from Sam Tobin-Hochstadt:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[Perhaps] Q* qualifies as =E2=80=
=9CAGI=E2=80=9D [artificial general intelligence] and OpenAI=E2=80=99s inve=
stment documents give the investors (specifically Microsoft) rights only to=
 pre-AGI technology. So from now on OpenAI products will be available to ev=
eryone, not just investors.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I am not sure about the details, but OpenAI <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33512585.284432/aHR0=
cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL291ci1zdHJ1Y3R1cmU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBca0b6a96" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;"> says that</a> AGI =E2=80=9Cis excluded from IP licenses and other =
commercial terms with Microsoft, which only apply to pre-AGI technology,=E2=
=80=9D and anyway its ultimate mission is to build AGI =E2=80=9Cfor the ben=
efit of humanity.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s possible that the plan is for=C2=A0=
OpenAI to=C2=A0ruthlessly commercialize chatbots to make money to build AGI=
, but once it has built AGI it has to give it away for the benefit of human=
ity.=C2=A0So an OpenAI product that moves=C2=A0<em>too=C2=A0</em>close to a=
rtificial general intelligence might be=C2=A0<em>bad=C2=A0</em>for valuatio=
n; it cuts down the time you can profit from chatbots.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or, more generally, several readers argued=C2=
=A0that if you think that AGI will revolutionize economic life, usher in a =
post-capitalist paradise, enslave or eradicate=C2=A0humanity, etc., then ac=
hieving AGI makes your investment in OpenAI worth less. =E2=80=9CIt may be =
difficult to know what role money will play in a=C2=A0post-AGI=C2=A0world,=
=E2=80=9D OpenAI also says. I am not sure that that should be a reason to r=
educe your valuation of OpenAI specifically =E2=80=94=C2=A0like, that=E2=80=
=99s bad for your shares in ExxonMobil or whatever too, or for your holding=
s of cash for that matter =E2=80=94=C2=A0but, sure, a possibility.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One more, from another reader:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">OpenAI worth &lt; $86B for tech re=
asons is definitely possible. It can solve a few math word problems and now=
 the researchers think they have AGI? Who are these rubes?</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean that=E2=80=99s probably unfair but it=
=E2=80=99s also funny.</p>
